  "prompt": "What is the most underrated romantic movie?",
  "response": "One highly underrated romantic movie is \"Before Sunrise\" (1995), directed by Richard Linklater. The film follows two strangers, Jesse and C\u00e9line, who meet on a train in Europe and decide to spend one evening together in Vienna. Their deep conversations and emerging connection are beautifully captured, highlighting the magic of spontaneous romance and the fleeting nature of time. Despite its critical acclaim and strong cult following, it often flies under the radar compared to more mainstream romantic films. The film's sequels, \"Before Sunset\" and \"Before Midnight,\" further explore the characters' evolving relationship, making it a profound exploration of love over time.",
